The '''Centre for the Study of Contemporary Islam''' (full official name in [[Italian language|Italian]] '''Centro Studi sull'Islam Contemporaneo''', CSIC) is an Italian institute specialised in Islamic studies.

It is a private association and its headquarters are in [[Rome]].

The Centre's activities branch out in two main directions: [[MENA]] and [[Asia-Pacific|APAC]] programmes, making research, publications, and events. CSIC is an impartial scientific benchmark for all those interested in international issues: from members of the political and cultural worlds to operators in the business community, public administrations, international bodies and [[Non-governmental organization|non governmental organisations]].

