{{Infobox University |name = Colleges of Applied Sciences |image = |native_name = |latin_name = |image_name = |image_size = |motto = |mottoeng = |established = '''2007''' |type = Public |endowment = |staff = |faculty = |president = |provost = |principal = |rector = |chancellor = |vice_chancellor = |dean = |head_label = |head = |students = |undergrad = 7,648 |postgrad = |doctoral = |city = [[Rustaq]], [[Ibri]], [[Salalah]], [[Nizwa]], [[Sohar]], [[Sur, Oman|Sur]] |state = |country = [[Sultanate of Oman]] |coor = |campus = |free_label = |free = |colors = |colours = |mascot = |nickname = |affiliations = |website = {{URL|www.cas.edu.om/}} }}
The '''Colleges of Applied Sciences''' are six government owned and operated colleges located the [[Sultanate of Oman]]. The colleges have locations in [[Rustaq]], [[Ibri]], [[Salalah]], [[Nizwa]], [[Sohar]], and [[Sur,Oman|Sur]]. The colleges are the only ones in the country which fall under the Ministry of Higher Education.
The Colleges of Applied Sciences offer [[bachelor's degree]] programs in [[Information Technology]], [[Graphic Design|Design]], [[Communication Studies]], and [[Business Administration|International Business Administration]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Directorate General of Colleges of Applied Sciences|url=http://cas.edu.om/Pages/About-Directorate--General-of-Colleges-of-Applied-Sciences.aspx|website=College of Applied Sciences|publisher=MoHE|accessdate=11 June 2016}}</ref>
In 2015 students enrolled in the six colleges total 7,648,<ref>{{cite web|title=Statistics|url=https://www.cas.edu.om/Pages/Statistics-Department-.aspx|website=College of Applied Sciences|publisher=MoHE|accessdate=11 June 2016}}</ref> with students including both males and females.
