'''Kangaroo Kids International Preschool (KKIP)''' is a chain of schools run by the Kangaroo Kids Education Ltd. (KKEL) [[Mumbai]], [[India]]. It is [[India]]’s largest [[pre-kindergarten]] and K12 school chains.<ref name="livemint">{{cite news|last1=Choudhary|first1=Anuradha|title=Kangaroo Kids raises $20 million from Gaja Capital|url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/CTaoSpWMblHrB8aJ8uguOJ/Kangaroo-Kids-raises-20-million-from-Gaja-Capital.html|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|date=22 March 2017}}</ref> The school imparts pre-school education to more than 9,000 students across 79 branches at 20 cities in [[India]], [[Dubai]], and [[Maldives]].<ref name="vccircle">{{cite news|last1=|first1=|title=Kangaroo Kids Preschool|url=http://events.vccircle.com/content/kangaroo-kids|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=[[VCCircle]]|date=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=|first1=|title=Gaja Capital in talks to invest ₹135 crore in Kangaroo Kids|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/education/gaja-capital-in-talks-to-invest-135-crore-in-kangaroo-kids/article9598481.ece|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=[[Business Line]]|date=23 March 2017}}</ref>
==History== Kangaroo Kids International Preschool was established by Lina Ashar in 1993.<ref name="vccircle"/><ref name="brandequity">{{cite news|last1=Upadhyay |first1=Toyoja |title=Marketing lessons Kangaroo Kids can teach you|url=https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/marketing/marketing-lessons-kangaroo-kids-can-teach-you/65710145|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=[[The Economic Times]]|date=7 September 2018}}</ref> The first Kangaroo Kids Preschool was started in [[Bandra]] in a 650 sq. ft. [[Mumbai]] apartment with a small batch of 25 students and presently Kangaroo Kids is a chain of 70 preschools across [[India]] as well as in [[Dubai]], [[Qatar]], and the [[Maldives]].<ref name="livemint"/><ref>{{cite news|last1=Dsilva|first1=Jeetha|title=Learning by doing: fun school with a price tag|url=https://www.livemint.com/Companies/pbUqasf1rbQPw7kSsFtaWP/Learning-by-doing-fun-school-with-a-price-tag.html|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]|date=2 July 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Anand|first1=Shilpa Nair |title=On a different path|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/education/school/on-a-different-path/article5032215.ece|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=18 August 2013}}</ref>
==Academic and curriculum== Kangaroo Kids Club facilitates action-based learning that focuses on creating a fun-filled learning environment for all students. The sessions are designed to encourage the exploratory side in toddlers and provide multisensory stimulation through visual, auditory and kinesthetic programmes.<ref name="vccircle"/> Kangaroo Kids Preschool is recognized by mainstream schools as an institution that produces creative, confident and eager learners. The preschools are in the process of developing learning apps for children that will help engage the child with integrating the curriculum.<ref name="brandequity"/>
==Facilities== The preschool has [[air-conditioned]] classrooms, 24 hours [[CCTV]] surveillance, reading zone, multi PlayStation with [[sandpit]], toddler play zone, and an [[audio-visual]] room with [[Projector]], Splash Pool, Child-friendly washrooms and pantry.<ref>{{cite news|last1=|first1= |title=Kangaroo Kids, Greater Kailash - EducationWorld|url=https://www.educationworld.in/kangaroo-kids-greater-kailash/|accessdate=16 October 2018|work=EducationWorld|date=}}</ref>
