'''Kevin Lang''' (born February 16, 1955) is a professor of Economics at [[Boston University]].  He is also an elected Fellow of the Society of Labor Economists and a Research Associate of the [[National Bureau of Economic Research]] (NBER).<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.bu.edu/experts/profiles/kevin-lang/ Kevin Lang » Public Relations | Blog Archive | Boston University<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  He is the author of ''Poverty and Discrimination'' and over 100 papers and articles on topics in [[Labor Economics]].<ref name=autogenerated1 /><ref>[http://press.princeton.edu/titles/8354.html Lang, K.: Poverty and Discrimination (eBook and Hardcover)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

Lang received his BA in Philosophy, Politics and Economics (PPE) from [[Oxford University]], his MSc in economics from the [[University of Montreal]], and his PhD in economics from the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] in 1982.  He went on to become an assistant professor at the [[University of California, Irvine]], and he spent a year serving as an [[John M. Olin Foundation|Olin Foundation]] Fellow at the NBER.  In 1987, he joined the faculty at Boston University, where he served as chair of the economics department from 2005-2009.<ref name=autogenerated1 /> His recent research has focused on the economics of labor markets and education,<ref>[http://www.mintpressnews.com/student-debt-reaches-new-high-professor-demands-increased-federal-assistance/52050/ Student Debt Reaches New High - Professor Demands Increased Federal Assistance<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> including topics such as discrimination, unemployment,<ref>[http://www.fairtest.org/new-research-good-reads New Research, Good Reads | FairTest<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> the relation between education and earnings,<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/opinion/editorials/article/For-profit-colleges-must-meet-standards-3688776.php For-profit colleges must meet standards - SFGate<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and the relation between [[housing prices]], taxes and local services.

Lang lives with his wife, Shulamit Kahn, in [[Brookline, Massachusetts]], where he is also active in local politics.  He served as an elected member of the Brookline School Committee from 1999-2009.<ref>[http://www.boston.com/news/local/articles/2009/03/29/departing_numbers_guy_likes_schools_odds/?page=full Brookline schools' retiring 'numbers guy' Kevin Lang upbeat about the future] - ''[[The Boston Globe]]''<!-- Bot generated title --></ref>

